hackathon-eligibility: Harvard-Westlake students from 9th-12th grade. Team sizes of up to four students per team in order to be eligible for prizes.
hackathon-rules: To be eligible to compete for prizes, all coding/implementation must be done during the 36-hour hackathon period at Harvard-Westlake school, and submitted before 4:15 pm on January 17th. You must have a team of at most four Harvard-Westlake students.

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: The members of team that made the best project will each win a mini 3D printer!
The members of the team that made the second best project will each win a smartwatch!
The members of the team that made the third best project will each win a quadcopter!

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion: Win a Pebble Classic Smart Watch!
